==English==

===Proper Noun===
'''Minix'''

# A computer operating system invented for teaching operating system principles. The name was invented by Andrew S. Tanenbaum as a contraction of mini-Unix. He created Minix to provide an operating system whose code and data structures could be studied in university courses after the owners of Unix, previously used for this purpose, withdrew permission for such use.

see also: Unix, Linux

